 :research/revision-note
 "2026-07-18: paper revised while submission is on hold in arXiv moderation.
  De-emphasized Williams STOC 2025 as the theoretical foundation (now cited
  as inspiration for the specific stride formula only; primary lineage is
  classical checkpointing -- Griewank-Walther 2000, Chen et al. 2016).
  Reframed value proposition as memory capability under constraint, not
  speed. Added real M2-M6 findings: end-to-end correctness (exact token
  match), real 2-method-validated decode cost (2.2x-3.7x), competitive
  comparison vs kvpress (StreamingLLM/Knorm/SnapKV score 0% at ~90%
  compression), MLA composability gap (cross-ecosystem confirmed, both
  HF and mlx-lm skip absorbed caching), and the Apple Silicon
  memory-capability validation (mmap vs naive offload; GLM-4-9B-Chat-1M
  real capability-unlock numbers). Not yet resubmitted to arXiv (requires
  human login action); published to the HF dataset in the interim -- see
  :research/related :hf-dataset."
